what is a delay in the heart my year old son was in the hospital over the weekend with seizure type symptoms some of the doctors told me his heart has a delay one cardiology report states this and the other report says it's normal there are conditions such as ectopic beat and extrasystoles that cause what appears to be one or more skipped beats generally it's not dangerous unless the skipping occurs so much that the person loses consciousness or gets dizzy from the temporary lack of blood flow to the brain and falls or has an accident while driving there are procedures that can be used to stop the condition if it is troublesome a guy i know had it done recently and also former prime minister tony blair had it done a couple of years ago in my friend's case he was falling down and getting hurt and he couldn't drive a car he's apparently fine now hasn't fallen and is back behind the wheel Cardiac arrhythmia Traumatic brain injury Stroke Myocardial infarction Epilepsy Hypoglycemia Seizure Heart First aid Panic attack Drowning Atrial fibrillation Intracranial pressure Cephalic disorder Bleeding Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Pneumonia Aspartame Ventricular fibrillation The Inside Head injury Chronic fatigue syndrome Diabetes mellitus Prostate cancer Concussion of the brain Anxiety Narcolepsy Maprotiline Ebola Atherosclerosis Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Hypertension Miscarriage Electroconvulsive therapy Clomipramine Intravenous therapy Insulin Doctor Who (Enemy Within) Constitution of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus Urinary incontinence Hyperthermia Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Banned episodes of Pok__mon Hypertrophic cardiomyopathy Suicide methods Cerebral palsy Decompression sickness Atrial septal defect Cardiology Artificial pacemaker Folic acid Asperger syndrome Obstetrics Psychosis Prime Minister of the United Kingdom Shock Dehydration Controversies in autism Indianapolis 500 Stomach cancer Glossary of medical terms related to communications disorder